12/01/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The Democratic Party's (DS) candidate for prime minister, Bozidar Djelic, invited incumbent Vojislav Kostunica of the Democratic Party of Serbia to participate in a TV debate on economic policy. Djelic, a former finance minister, insisted that voters should understand the economic agenda of the two main parties in the so-called democratic bloc. He also pledged that a DS-led government would resume negotiations on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU within three months. Elections in Serbia are scheduled for January 21st. (Blic, Politika - 12/01/07)
